Opposition parties in Ireland are to hold crisis talks to bring down the Brian Cowen-led government after the Green Party pulled out of government yesterday; Fianna Fáil no longer has a leader and it no longer has a coalition partner. (BBC)Minister for Finance Brian Lenihan, Jnr and Minister for Tourism, Culture and Sport Mary Hanafin formally announce their candidacies for the leadership of Fianna Fáil following yesterday's resignation of Brian Cowen as party leader. (RTÉ) (The Irish Times)